  "texts": [
    "By masking them, we aim to learn debiased representations from the data during pre-training.",
    "Dale-Chall Easy Words List comprises 2950 words that are reliably understood by students (Chall and Dale, 1995).",
    "Of these, 4.85% overlap with stopwords, which we subsequently remove.",
    "We then mask the remaining 2807 words at a slightly higher masking rate of 0.20 to prioritize the linguistic simplicity specific to children.",
    "Other Words In our KidLM corpus (§2.1), it is unsurprising that stopwords are dominant, accounting for 45.93%, while Dale-Chall Easy words make up 21.82%, and other words constitute 32.45%."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Dale-Chall Easy Words List comprises 2950 words that are reliably understood by students (Chall and Dale, 1995)."
